{
  "documentMetadata": {
    "title": "Endocarditis, Coagulase-Negative Staphylococci",
    "lastUpdated": "2025-04-22",
    "sourceFile": "Endocarditis, Coagulase-Negative Staphylococci.pdf"
  },
  "content": [
    {
      "type": "header",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Clinical Setting"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "items": [
        "Specific therapy for coagulase-negative Staphylococcal endocarditis.",
        "Prosthetic valve.",
        "Signs and symptoms of endocarditis. Positive blood cultures for Staph. epidermidis, other coagulase-negative species of staphylococci."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "header",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Etiologies"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "items": [
        "Staphylococcus epidermidis",
        "Coagulase-negative staphylococci"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "header",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Primary Regimens"
    },
    {
      "type": "drugRegimen",
      "regimenData": {
        "intent": "treatment",
        "condition": "MRSE",
        "components": [
          {
            "drug": "Vancomycin",
            "dose": "15-20 mg/kg",
            "route": "IV",
            "frequency": "q8-12h",
            "notes": "to achieve preferred target AUC24 400-600 µg/mL x hr (see vancomycin AUC dosing calculator; alternative is trough of 15-20 µg/mL)",
            "connector": "+"
          },
          {
            "drug": "Rifampin",
            "dose": "600-900 mg/day",
            "route": "po/IV",
            "notes": "(see Antimicrobial Stewardship) in 2-3 divided doses",
            "connector": "+"
          },
          {
            "drug": "Gentamicin",
            "dose": "1 mg/kg",
            "route": "IV",
            "frequency": "q8h"
          }
        ],
        "durationDetail": {
          "fixedDuration": "6 weeks and 2 weeks"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "drugRegimen",
      "regimenData": {
        "intent": "treatment",
        "condition": "MSSE",
        "components": [
          {
            "drug": "Nafcillin",
            "dose": "2 gm",
            "route": "IV",
            "frequency": "q4h",
            "connector": "or"
          },
          {
            "drug": "Oxacillin",
            "dose": "2 gm",
            "route": "IV",
            "frequency": "q4h"
          }
        ],
        "notes": "can be substituted for Vancomycin"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "header",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Alternative Regimens"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "None"
    },
    {
      "type": "header",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Antimicrobial Stewardship"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "items": [
        "Wait 3-5 days after starting vancomycin/gentamicin before starting rifampin, to decrease bacterial density and thus minimize risk of selecting for rifampin resistance."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "header",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Comments"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "items": [
        "Monitor renal function carefully on Vancomycin/Gentamicin-containing regimens.",
        "AHA endocarditis treatment guidelines: Circulation 132: 1435, 2015."
      ]
    }
  ]
}